item.description:
casey neistat film school enrollment at https://monthly.com/casey
my 30-day online filmmaking & storytelling class just launched! Enrollment is open now until December 27. the class is a hands-on, 30-day learning experience, designed to teach you everything I know about filmmaking and storytelling, i'm going to share with you my entire creative process from start to finish. You're going to follow along with me as I create 2 brand new movies from scratch... from how I come up the ideas, all the way through exporting the final videos.
over the month, you'll follow along with me and my process, side by side, and you will leave the class with 2 original, shareable films of your own. its is the class I wish I had when I was starting out. The class officially starts on January 10, 2022, and it will only run a few times per year, so claim your spot if you're interested

item.title: Davis vs Cruz HIGHLIGHTS: December 15, 2021 | PBC on Showtime PPV
item.description:
Boxing superstar and five-time world champion Gervonta â€œTankâ€ Davis put his boxing skills on display, winning a rousing 12-round round unanimous decision over the relentless Isaac â€œPitbullâ€ Cruz to retain his WBA Lightweight World Title in front of a star-studded, sellout crowd of 15,850 at STAPLES Center live on SHOWTIME Pay-Per-View.
There was no feeling-out process in the first. Cruz charged at the defending champion, pinning him against the ropes and wailing away.
â€œThatâ€™s my style. â€˜Pitbullâ€™ is always going to be on the attack,â€ said Cruz. â€œI think we retained rhythm from the start to the end.â€
Davis found his rhythm in the second and third, circling the ring and walking Cruz into shots. In the fourth, Cruz concentrated his attack on the body, pounding Davisâ€™ ribs.
The 27-year-old Baltimore native turned on the power in the fourth, alternating between the right hook and left cross behind his southpaw stance. More punishing blows came from Davis during the fifth.
â€œHeâ€™s a shorter fighter, so I was throwing down on the top of his head,â€ said Davis. â€œI hit him with my knuckle and messed it up. I hurt my hand in the sixth round. No matter if the opponent is taller or shorter, Iâ€™ve got to get through it. Heâ€™s a warrior. Even though he didnâ€™t win, a star was born tonight.â€
â€œIt was right around the fifth round I saw that his hand wasnâ€™t working correctly,â€ Cruz observed.
Davis boxed beautifully in the middle rounds, firing quick shots and pivoting away from the return fire. A right hook in the eighth briefly buzzed Cruz and brought the audience to their feet. But just when it appeared as if the fight was slipping away, Cruz fought fire with fire, landing a flush uppercut seconds before the bell.
The 23-year-old Mexican picked up the pace in the latter rounds, keeping Davis on his toes and pounding away. Davis held his own, fighting back on even terms until the fightâ€™s end.
Naturally, Cruz believed he deserved the victory.
â€œViva Mexico. I have nothing to say, the fans are speaking on who won this fight,â€ he said.
Following a successful title defense, Davis said heâ€™s ready for all comers.
â€œL.A., we did it for Kobe,â€ said Davis. â€œAt the beginning of the fight, he came on strong. I felt as the fight was going, he was breaking down. But I hurt my hand, so I wasnâ€™t able to get him out of there.
â€œWhatever the best opportunity is for me, Iâ€™ll do it. All of them guys are easy work. Iâ€™m the top dog.â€

item.description:
Watch the Fortnite Chapter 3 Season 1 Flipped trailer!
The Fortnite Island has been flipped and a new one has been revealed.
Due to a particularly cold winter, the first thing youâ€™ll notice about the Island is that the western halfâ€™s a wintry biome. Perhaps stop by the suburban Greasy Grove, the industrial Logjam Lumberyard, and other locales. Like warmer weather? To the east are the tropics, with coastal keys, palm trees, and weathered sights to see. Although The Seven have outposts all throughout the Island, the tropics are home to their home, the â€œSanctuary.â€ This compound is right next to the coast, where you can get a clear view of the colossal rock statue of The Foundation. And speaking of colossal, the towering, web-covered Daily Bugle building is also in the area. Like even warmer weather? In the south you can find the desert (some of it decorated in snow), but this desert isnâ€™t barren on interesting places. Go off-road racing at Chonkerâ€™s Speedway, revel in cozy living at Condo Canyon, and something that will wet even the driest eyes, â€œcome on downâ€ to the returning Butter Barn. A fresh slate of weapons awaits you on the Island. Hereâ€™s a rundown of whatâ€™s new!
Ranger Assault Rifle
Made for distance! The Ranger Assault Rifle is forceful at medium range and quite capable at long range.
MK-Seven Assault Rifle Built from The Sevenâ€™s technology, the MK-Seven Assault Rifle is a medium- to long-range weapon with a high rate of fire. This Assault Rifle has a sight you can use while aiming. Align your target with the sightâ€™s red dot! If you want something even better, confront The Foundation for a special version of the MK-Seven Assault Rifle, sporting a slightly faster fire rate.
Striker Pump Shotgun The Striker Pump Shotgun shoots a whole lot of pellets and boasts high burst damage. Aimâ€¦ then strike!
Auto Shotgun An automatic ally that lays down some serious firepower. The Auto Shotgun may not deal as much damage as the Striker Pump per shot, but it has a faster fire rate and reloads two shells at a time.
Stinger SMG Appropriately named, the Stinger SMG deals high damage to both opponents and structures. It stings at medium range more than one may expect!
Sidearm Pistol A trusty weapon to have by your side, the Sidearm Pistol is an accurate weapon that deals high damage at medium range and high headshot damage at close range. Donâ€™t underestimate it!
Hunter Bolt-Action Sniper The Hunter Bolt-Action Sniper deals high damage and can shoot three shots per clip. Get a second chance if you donâ€™t land your shot the first time! (And a third... just in case.)
